        "content": "<p>alexcrichton opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13647\">PR #13647</a> from <code>alexcrichton:back44</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:release-44.0.0</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This commit fixes a file descriptor leak in the WASIp1 implementation of<br>\n<code>fd_renumber</code> in the <code>wasmtime-wasi</code> crate. Notably the previous<br>\nimplementation did not fully close the file descriptor being<br>\nrenumbered-to which meant that the host's resources for the file,<br>\nincluding the file descriptor, stayed alive. The fix here is to validate<br>\nboth fds exist and then delegate to the <code>fd_close</code> call to close the<br>\ndestination.</p>\n<p>This additionally updates the behavior of <code>fd_renumber</code> when renumbering<br>\nto fds that weren't previously open to match the <code>main</code> branch which<br>\nnotably rejects these calls.</p>\n</blockquote>",
